{
  "text": "Both the ST 2 model and the resource sharing theory propose that T1 processing affects the consolidation of T2 during the AB, which is supported by behavioral (e.g., [CITATION_1] and EEG [CITATION_2] data. In addition to the unidirectional influence of T1 on T2, however, resource sharing also argues that there is mutual interference during the AB, as T1 and T2 compete indirectly through the amount of resource allocated to them. The behavioral and EEG data from Experiment 2, however, do not support this hypothesis. These data suggest that T2 does not influence T1 if presented at Lag 3 or Lag 8. In addition, there is no effect on T1 processing whether an AB occurs or not.",
